.SH NAME
sigemptyset \- initialize n' empty a signal set
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
\fB#include <signal.h>
.br
.sp
int sigemptyset(sigset_t *\fP\fIset\fP\fB); \fP
\fB
.br
\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Da \fIsigemptyset\fP() function initializes tha signal set pointed
to by \fIset\fP, such dat all signals defined in
IEEE\ Std\ 1003.1-2001 is excluded.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.LP
Upon successful completion, \fIsigemptyset\fP() shall return 0; otherwise,
it shall return -1 n' set \fIerrno\fP ta indicate
the error.
.SH ERRORS
.LP
No errors is defined.
.LP
\fIDa followin sections is informative.\fP
